abstract: The restrained approach of Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. to what he called his “ill-defined responsibilities” did not please liberals. But it insulated him from combustible confrontations.
snippet: The restrained approach of Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. to what he called his “ill-defined responsibilities” did not please liberals. But it insulated him from combustible confrontations.
lead_paragraph: Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. has returned to his day job, and he must be relieved.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg has been on defense all weekend as his Democratic presidential rivals attacked him on everything from his struggle to connect with black voters to accepting campaign contributions from large donors in an effort to blunt any momentum heading into Tuesday's New Hampshire primary.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg has been on defense all weekend as his Democratic presidential rivals attacked him on everything from his struggle to connect with black voters to accepting campaign contributions from large donors in an effort to blunt any momentum...
lead_paragraph: DOVER, N.H. — Pete Buttigieg has been on defense all weekend as his Democratic presidential rivals attacked him on everything from his struggle to connect with black voters to accepting campaign contributions from large donors in an effort to blunt any momentum heading into Tuesday's New Hampshire primary.
headline_main: Buttigieg on Defense as Rivals Aim to Blunt His Momentum
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg on Defense as Rivals Aim to Blunt His Momentum

abstract: The point of the attacks was not to set off mass defections between the left and the center, but rather to consolidate support on one side of the party or the other.
snippet: The point of the attacks was not to set off mass defections between the left and the center, but rather to consolidate support on one side of the party or the other.
lead_paragraph: HOOKSETT, N.H. — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont and former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., clashed throughout the day on Sunday, in a combative display of their determination to treat the upcoming New Hampshire primary as a two-person race, with former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. continuing to struggle.

abstract: With decision time just two days away, scores of New Hampshire voters on Sunday — and some political tourists — flocked to school gyms and hotel ballrooms to get a glimpse of the Democratic candidates as they made their closing arguments

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg narrowly beat rival Bernie Sanders in Iowa in the race for delegates, according to projected national delegate allocations released by the Iowa Democratic Party on Sunday.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg narrowly beat rival Bernie Sanders in Iowa in the race for delegates, according to projected national delegate allocations released by the Iowa Democratic Party on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg narrowly beat rival Bernie Sanders in Iowa in the race for delegates, according to projected national delegate allocations released by the Iowa Democratic Party on Sunday.
headline_main: Buttigieg Edges Past Sanders in Iowa's National Delegate Race: State Party
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Edges Past Sanders in Iowa's National Delegate Race: State Party

abstract: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
snippet: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
lead_paragraph: It’s been a rough week for Democrats. President Trump is preening over his acquittal, his poll numbers and the economy, while the Democratic nomination race looks like a divided mess. Many Democratic voters are anxious that they have no great candidates, only those guaranteed to alienate one half of the party or the other.

abstract: Errors in the results have led The Times and others to refrain from calling the race, and the Sanders campaign manager said a partial recanvass of precincts could change the outcome.
snippet: Errors in the results have led The Times and others to refrain from calling the race, and the Sanders campaign manager said a partial recanvass of precincts could change the outcome.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Nearly a full week after the Iowa caucuses, the state Democratic Party on Sunday released results indicating that Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., was the winner after it updated data from 55 precincts. But errors in the result tabulations have led several news organizations, including The New York Times, to refrain from calling the race.
